      "30g protein, 160 calories, $1.50–2.00 per shake. We break down whether it actually earns its place in your rotation.",
    href: "/reviews/premier-protein-shake-review",
    badge: "Top Pick",
    rating: 4,
    priceRange: "$1.50–2.00/shake",
    category: "Protein",
  },
  {
    title: "Kodiak Waffles Review: Worth It for Fitness?",
    description:
      "~12g protein per waffle, whole grain oats, and a taste that doesn't make you feel like you're dieting.",
    href: "/reviews/kodiak-waffles-review",
    badge: "4.5/5",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$5–7/box",
    category: "Food",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Resistance Bands Under $30 for Dorm Workouts",
    description:
      "No gym? No problem. Three picks that cover every resistance level for under $30 total.",
    href: "/reviews/best-resistance-bands-dorm-workout",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$14–30",
    category: "Equipment",
  },
  {
    title: "Creatine for Beginners: Do You Actually Need It?",
    description:
      "The most research-backed supplement in fitness, under $0.40/day. Here's what it does and how to take it.",
    href: "/reviews/creatine-for-beginners",
    badge: "5/5 Value",
    rating: 5,
    priceRange: "$15–25/tub",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Pre-Workout for College Students in 2025",
    description:
      "Three picks at different price points — from a $30 budget option to a fully transparent label formula.",
    href: "/reviews/best-pre-workout-college-students",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4,
    priceRange: "$30–55",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "How to Build a Home Gym Under $200",
    description:
      "Five pieces of gear, ~$150 total, fits in a closet. A full-body program included.",
    href: "/guides/home-gym-under-200",
    badge: "Guide",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$124–164 total",
    category: "Guides",
  },
  {
    title: "Chick-fil-A Grilled Nuggets: Good for Bulking?",
    description:
      "25–38g protein per order. Full macro breakdown, cost-per-gram analysis, and best combos by goal.",
    href: "/guides/chick-fil-a-grilled-nuggets-macros",
    badge: "Guide",
    rating: 4,
    priceRange: "$6–8/order",
    category: "Nutrition",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Blender Bottle for Protein Shakes (2025)",
    description:
      "Three shakers reviewed on leak-proofing, mixability, cleaning, and price. No clumps, no backpack disasters.",
    href: "/reviews/best-blender-bottle-protein-shakes",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$10–18",
    category: "Gear",
  },
  {
    title: "MyProtein vs ON Gold Standard: Which Is Worth It?",
    description:
      "Full side-by-side on macros, cost per serving, mixability, and third-party testing so you buy the right tub.",
    href: "/reviews/myprotein-vs-on-gold-standard",
    badge: "Comparison",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$38–60/tub",
    category: "Protein",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Whey Protein for Cutting (College Student Edition)",
    description:
      "Three low-calorie, high-protein isolates compared on macros, taste, and cost — so you keep muscle while leaning out.",
    href: "/reviews/best-whey-protein-cutting-college-students",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$35–55/tub",
    category: "Protein",
  },
  {
    title: "Is Creatine Safe for 18 Year Olds?",
    description:
      "What 30 years of research actually says about creatine safety for young adults — no bro-science, just the facts.",
    href: "/guides/is-creatine-safe-18-year-olds",
    badge: "Guide",
    rating: 5,
    priceRange: "~$0.40/day",
    category: "Guides",
  },
  {
    title: "Cheap Meal Prep for College Students (Bulking on $50/Week)",
    description:
      "A full week of 3,000+ calorie bulking meals for under $50. Grocery list, prep order, and macro totals included.",
    href: "/guides/cheap-meal-prep-college-students-bulking",
    badge: "Guide",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$40–50/week",
    category: "Guides",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Protein Bars Under $2 (That Actually Taste Good)",
    description:
      "Four picks under $2 per bar with 20g+ protein — ranked by cost, macros, taste, and where to buy them cheapest.",
    href: "/reviews/best-protein-bars-under-2-dollars",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$1.25–1.99/bar",
    category: "Protein",
  },
  {
    title: "Liquid IV Review: Is It Actually Worth It for Working Out?",
    description:
      "Everyone on campus is drinking Liquid IV. Here's whether the hype — and the price — holds up for college students who train.",
    href: "/reviews/liquid-iv-review-worth-it-working-out",
    badge: "Review",
    rating: 4,
    priceRange: "$1.50–2.00/stick",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "Creatine Gummies vs Powder: Which Is Actually Better?",
    description:
      "Gummies are everywhere on TikTok, but a hidden dosing problem makes most of them a bad deal. Here's what to buy.",
    href: "/reviews/creatine-gummies-vs-powder",
    badge: "Comparison",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$0.25 vs $1.50/serving",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "Ghost Whey vs Dymatize ISO100: Which Protein Is Worth It?",
    description:
      "Ghost has the best flavors in the game. ISO100 has the cleaner macros and lower price. Here's which one to buy.",
    href: "/reviews/ghost-whey-vs-dymatize-iso100",
    badge: "Comparison",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$45–55/tub",
    category: "Protein",
  },
  {
    title: "Alani Nu Pre Workout Review: Is the Hype Real?",
    description:
      "Alani Nu blew up on TikTok and now it's everywhere. Here's whether the 200mg caffeine + L-theanine formula actually holds up.",
    href: "/reviews/alani-nu-pre-workout-review",
    badge: "Review",
    rating: 4,
    priceRange: "$1.30–1.50/serving",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "Best Electrolyte Drinks for Working Out (Budget Picks for 2025)",
    description:
      "Nuun, Liquid IV, LMNT, and Ultima — ranked by value and electrolyte content so you stop paying $3 for Gatorade.",
    href: "/reviews/best-electrolyte-drinks-working-out",
    badge: "Roundup",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$0.55–2.00/serving",
    category: "Supplements",
  },
  {
    title: "Ashwagandha for College Students: Does It Actually Help with Stress?",
    description:
      "The research on ashwagandha is more solid than most trending supplements. Here's what it does, what it doesn't, and how to buy it right.",
    href: "/guides/ashwagandha-college-students-stress",
    badge: "Guide",
    rating: 4.5,
    priceRange: "$15–25 / 2 months",
    category: "Guides",
  },
];
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">For college students on a budget</p>
      <h1>Train smarter.<br />Spend less.</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Honest reviews of protein, supplements, and gear — ranked by value, not by who paid us.
        Every pick comes with real macro numbers and real price breakdowns.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/guides/home-gym-under-200" class="btn-primary">Build a $200 Home Gym</a>
        <a href="/reviews/creatine-for-beginners" class="btn-secondary">Start with Creatine</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Reviews Grid -->
  <section class="reviews-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2 class="section-title">All Reviews & Guides</h2>
      <div class="reviews-grid">
        {featuredReviews.map((review) => (
          <ProductCard
            title={review.title}
            description={review.description}
            href={review.href}
            badge={review.badge}
            rating={review.rating}
            priceRange={review.priceRange}
            category={review.category}
          />
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
    color: #f8fafc;
    padding: 5rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #f97316;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #f97316;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: #ea6c00;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: transparent;
    color: #cbd5e1;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    border: 1px solid #334155;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    color: #f8fafc;
    border-color: #64748b;
  }

  /* Reviews grid */
  .reviews-section {
    padding: 4rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .reviews-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .reviews-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .reviews-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 3rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
